# Generating a SSL certificate signing request (CSR) on IIS7 Windows 2008

Follow these instructions to generate a SSL certificate signing request (CSR) on IIS7 Windows 2008


1. Open the Internet Information Services (IIS) Manager. From the Start button select Programs >> >>Administrative Tools >> Internet Information Services Manager.


2. In the IIS Manager, select the server node on the top left under Connections.
3. In the Features pane (the middle pane), double-click the Server Certificates.

```diagram

```


4. From the Actions pane on the top right, select Create Certificate Request. The Distinguished Name Properties dialog box will appear.

```diagram

```

5. Here you enter the Information as per provided by customer. Suppose the domain to be www.websitetest.com

6. Click next after filling all the details.

7. The next screen of the wizard asks you to choose cryptography options. The default Microsoft RSA SChannel Cryptography Provider is fine and a key bit-length of 2048.

```diagram

```

8. Finally, specify a file name for the certificate request. This text file is the CSR file to be send to the Certificate Authority. In this case it is websitetestcsr.txt.


9. Click Finish, and you are done.
